content.description: Starts on sloppy bulge with pocket to rail. Easy climbing with positive holds and good feet. Crux down low.
content.location: Route is just right of Lost and Found.

content.description: Crux is towards the last two bolts. Positive holds with a few slab like moves.
content.location: Third route from the left. Right most on main face.

content.description: Slightly technical 5.9 with relatively positive holds. Starts with Side pulls over sloppy bulge to somewhat technical climbing.

climbs.name: The Last Marker Always Goes Bad

content.description: Grab a nice left hand jug and a small right hand hold and do a couple of longer pulls on medium size holds to get established on the main part of the wall.  Follow a few small holds to much easier ground heading to the anchor.
content.location: The left route on this bit of wall and the most left route at Walla Walla.

content.description: Small relatively positive holds with technical moves. A slightly thought provoking route.
content.location: Around the right side of the main face. The right most route at the crag.

content.description: Another rare Charleston moderate at this little crag.  Certainly not a classic, but fun nonetheless.  Grade is my guess from doing it twice, somewhere in the 10A range (5.9-10b)
content.protection:
5 Stainless Bolts to anchor with Stainless Fixe Supershut and Mussy

content.location: Far Left Route at Walla Walla; 10 feet left of Lost and Found

climbs.name: All My Rowdy Friends Have Settled Down

content.description: Get established on the wall and grab a large jug pocket, do a couple steep and long pulls between three more jugs and transition to more technical face climbing to a shared anchor.
content.location: This is the right line on the small wall that is the far left side of the Walla Walla formation.  About 30 left of The 100th Monkey.

content.description:
Smaller wall that lies in the wash and is home of 4 moderate sport routes. Is mostly shaded past noon. The wall is sharp grey limestone.  

  The routes from left to right: 

  Lost and Found - 5.9+   Where's my Dog - 5.8   Nighttime Shenanigans - 5.8   Just the Tip - 5.10b
